            "description": "One of the four example graphs of Fig. 3: a two-loop two-point function depending on the single dimensionless variable $x=p^2/m^2$, containing the equal-mass sunrise as a subtopology. Solid internal lines carry mass $m$ and dashed internal lines are massless; the external legs are on shell. The paper does not list explicit propagator momenta for this figure, so the propagator list, edge set, and kinematics are reported as null. The Picard-Fuchs analysis yields exactly one irreducible second-order factor (the one associated to the sunrise subtopology); all other factors are first order. Once the variable is changed from $x$ to the modular parameter $\\tau$ of the sunrise elliptic curve and the master integrals are rescaled appropriately, the system of differential equations is brought into $\\varepsilon$-form and solved order by order in $\\varepsilon$ in terms of iterated integrals of modular forms of $\\Gamma_1(6)$.",
